<br>
On a cleric CH rotation on Avatar of War for example, a CH hits the MT every third second or so. Our MT has around 7500 hp usually.<br>
<br>
This would mean that a &quot;druid ch&quot; rotation would require a spell to land on MT every second (3k heal). This in turn would require flawless connections, timings, and at least triple the druids.<br>
<br>
As an xp group spell, it's a great addition. As a raid spell, it's uses are limited. It's too slow for spot heals, it heals too little for a rotation, the best use I can see for it is to put up a second rotation for druid ch's running alongside the cleric ch's instead of all the spot heals they do whenever it's needed. Yet I have a hard time picturing it.<br>
<br>
Don't even get me started on the shamans.. torporing clerics and mages are a better use of their time, and chloroblast/torpor combination probably a better use of their mana in xp groups.<br>
<br>
